1
00:00:02,925 --> 00:00:05,525
Is this the rumored cactus?

2
00:00:05,525 --> 00:00:07,525
It's a cactus called "Golden Barrel"

3
00:00:07,525 --> 00:00:11,125
that takes 50 years to bear flowers.

4
00:00:11,125 --> 00:00:14,125
-What? 50 years? -Yeah.

5
00:00:14,125 --> 00:00:15,625
"Zenzo Sunada (66), a wealthy man" -I took care of it

6
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:17,725
since it was this small, right?

7
00:00:17,725 --> 00:00:20,325
After so many years, it grew to be this big

8
00:00:20,325 --> 00:00:23,025
and even blossomed with flowers.

9
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:27,525
Which means that you were raising it

10
00:00:27,525 --> 00:00:29,425
from the time you were about Ran's age?

11
00:00:29,425 --> 00:00:31,425
Exactly, sonny.

12
00:00:31,425 --> 00:00:36,125
Sonoko, you came to see it in the past with your father, you know.

13
00:00:36,125 --> 00:00:39,325
Really? I don't remember.

14
00:00:41,325 --> 00:00:43,325
It's not surprising that you don't remember,

15
00:00:43,325 --> 00:00:46,025
since you were still a toddler then.

16
00:00:46,025 --> 00:00:48,825
That's why.

17
00:00:48,825 --> 00:00:51,925
By the way, where's the flower that you're referring to?

18
00:00:51,925 --> 00:00:54,925
-It's right there. -Huh?

19
00:00:56,225 --> 00:00:58,925
It's enveloped by fluffy bird feather-like thorns at the top.

20
00:00:58,925 --> 00:01:00,925
The yellow flower.

21
00:01:00,925 --> 00:01:03,525
Really! How cute.

22
00:01:04,625 --> 00:01:06,925
I guess...

23
00:01:07,925 --> 00:01:09,625
True.

24
00:01:11,225 --> 00:01:13,225
The vivid colored memories of summer

25
00:01:13,225 --> 00:01:15,325
solve mysteries all season round.

26
00:01:15,325 --> 00:01:17,025
In a greenhouse under tight security,

27
00:01:17,025 --> 00:01:19,125
there're rare cactuses with stingy thorns.

28
00:01:19,125 --> 00:01:20,825
He sees through the one and only truth.

29
00:01:20,825 --> 00:01:22,825
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

30
00:01:22,825 --> 00:01:25,225
His name is Detective Conan!

31
00:03:06,127 --> 00:03:11,927
"Cactus Rhapsody"

32
00:03:12,827 --> 00:03:16,827
But what a large number of cactus you have here.

33
00:03:16,827 --> 00:03:19,527
I guess you've got some valuable ones here, too.

34
00:03:19,527 --> 00:03:21,727
Aren't you plagued by thieves at times?

35
00:03:21,727 --> 00:03:25,327
Well, there's a specially ordered alarm set up here.

36
00:03:26,727 --> 00:03:29,527
At night, I'm the only one who can cancel the alarm,

37
00:03:29,527 --> 00:03:31,727
since I have this card.

38
00:03:31,727 --> 00:03:34,727
It's sort of like the automatic wicket at the station.

39
00:03:34,727 --> 00:03:37,927
But, why do you keep it in your pocket?

40
00:03:38,827 --> 00:03:41,127
I keep whatever's important in here,

41
00:03:41,127 --> 00:03:43,527
that way I feel safe.

42
00:03:46,127 --> 00:03:47,727
Dad!

43
00:03:49,527 --> 00:03:51,127
What do you guys want?

44
00:03:51,127 --> 00:03:52,827
We heard from the lawyer!

45
00:03:52,827 --> 00:03:55,427
That you changed the will?

46
00:03:55,427 --> 00:03:58,227
Quiet! I've got guests!

47
00:03:58,227 --> 00:04:00,827
Shut up! Tell us what's going on!

48
00:04:00,827 --> 00:04:02,127
I'm not wasting my breath for something like that!

49
00:04:02,127 --> 00:04:03,627
Get out of here.

50
00:04:03,627 --> 00:04:06,327
My cactus are going to wither!

51
00:04:06,327 --> 00:04:08,927
No good, Yasuyuki. Let's take care of this later.

52
00:04:08,927 --> 00:04:10,127
Yeah.

53
00:04:10,127 --> 00:04:12,727
You're going to explain this to us later, understand?

54
00:04:12,727 --> 00:04:14,027
Gosh!

55
00:04:15,227 --> 00:04:16,527
Really, I tell you...

56
00:04:16,527 --> 00:04:19,727
The Golden Barrel finally blossomed, and yet...

57
00:04:22,627 --> 00:04:24,827
Yashiro!

58
00:04:24,827 --> 00:04:26,127
Where are you, Yashiro?

59
00:04:26,127 --> 00:04:29,627
Yes, sir.

60
00:04:29,627 --> 00:04:32,327
What seems to be the matter, sir?

61
00:04:32,327 --> 00:04:34,727
What the heck is that?

62
00:04:37,727 --> 00:04:41,027
I told you I don't use unglazed pottery planters!

63
00:04:41,027 --> 00:04:42,227
Put it away right this minute!

64
00:04:42,227 --> 00:04:44,427
I'm sorry.

65
00:04:46,027 --> 00:04:48,227
What a temper.

66
00:04:48,227 --> 00:04:50,427
Excuse me.

67
00:04:52,127 --> 00:04:54,627
We came at a bad time, didn't we?

68
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:57,527
He seems to have been known in his younger days as "Zenzo the Ogre"

69
00:04:57,527 --> 00:05:00,427
an aggressive wheeler-dealer.

70
00:05:00,427 --> 00:05:02,527
How embarrassing.

71
00:05:02,527 --> 00:05:06,327
I did shout at her, but she's a good worker, that Yashiro.

72
00:05:06,327 --> 00:05:08,927
She's a super good cook, too.

73
00:05:08,927 --> 00:05:11,127
Is that right?

74
00:05:11,127 --> 00:05:14,227
She's so different from my two sons.

75
00:05:14,227 --> 00:05:16,927
Okay, I'm going back to the house now,

76
00:05:16,927 --> 00:05:19,127
but why don't you all take your time looking around?

77
00:05:19,127 --> 00:05:20,827
-Yes, sir. -Yes, sir.

78
00:05:29,027 --> 00:05:31,627
What're you doing?

79
00:05:31,627 --> 00:05:32,927
Dad.

80
00:05:32,927 --> 00:05:35,327
I'm asking you what you're doing?

81
00:05:35,327 --> 00:05:37,727
What else?

82
00:05:37,727 --> 00:05:40,727
Unluckily, what you're looking for is here.

83
00:05:40,727 --> 00:05:42,127
"Will"

84
00:05:42,927 --> 00:05:47,327
Is it true that you're not dividing the inheritance to us?

85
00:05:47,327 --> 00:05:48,527
I've decided to donate everything

86
00:05:48,527 --> 00:05:50,927
to the Botanical Garden along with the cactuses.

87
00:05:50,927 --> 00:05:52,927
What?

88
00:05:54,327 --> 00:05:56,227
Not what you expected, eh?

89
00:05:56,227 --> 00:05:58,427
You're going to give your money up

90
00:05:58,427 --> 00:06:00,527
to your cactuses rather than your sons?

91
00:06:00,527 --> 00:06:01,927
Most naturally.

92
00:06:01,927 --> 00:06:03,827
A professional golfer, my foot.

93
00:06:03,827 --> 00:06:06,527
All you do is live off me despite being a grown man.

94
00:06:06,527 --> 00:06:08,227
I'm not giving you any money!

95
00:06:08,227 --> 00:06:09,827
What?

96
00:06:11,227 --> 00:06:14,427
Well, the flower was so small

97
00:06:14,427 --> 00:06:16,627
despite him asking us to come over and look at it, wasn't it?

98
00:06:16,627 --> 00:06:18,127
Not really.

99
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:20,727
He gave us an opportunity to see something really rare,

100
00:06:20,727 --> 00:06:22,427
so we should be grateful.

101
00:06:22,427 --> 00:06:25,927
That... I wonder what it is?

102
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:28,627
Isn't it a radiator for the water heater?

103
00:06:28,627 --> 00:06:32,027
I'm sure it's regulating the temperature in the greenhouse.

104
00:06:32,027 --> 00:06:33,427
I know, I know!

105
00:06:33,427 --> 00:06:35,427
If I remember correctly, the temperature's being controlled here.

106
00:06:35,427 --> 00:06:36,827
Hot!

107
00:06:37,827 --> 00:06:40,127
Hey, Sonoko. Are you all right?

108
00:06:41,527 --> 00:06:44,327
If so, what do I have to do to get you to go through

109
00:06:44,327 --> 00:06:46,527
with the original will?

110
00:06:46,527 --> 00:06:48,027
I have no intention of reversing the will

111
00:06:48,027 --> 00:06:49,527
unless you succeed my business!

112
00:06:49,527 --> 00:06:52,027
Are you telling me to quit golf?

113
00:06:52,027 --> 00:06:53,327
You're just a third tier player

114
00:06:53,327 --> 00:06:55,727
who's always defeated in the Monday qualifying anyway.

115
00:06:55,727 --> 00:06:58,427
How dare you, saying what you will...

116
00:06:58,427 --> 00:07:00,527
You took the words right out of my mouth!

117
00:07:00,527 --> 00:07:04,027
Okay then, I'll do as I please!

118
00:07:05,827 --> 00:07:07,727
You! What're you doing?

119
00:07:07,727 --> 00:07:09,227
Well, you see...

120
00:07:09,227 --> 00:07:13,527
I'll bet you came to ask for money as usual.

121
00:07:13,527 --> 00:07:14,927
Same to you!

122
00:07:14,927 --> 00:07:16,627
You won't get away trying to outdo me.

123
00:07:16,627 --> 00:07:19,327
-What? -Please stop!

124
00:07:19,327 --> 00:07:21,227
You're standing in front of your father's room, you know!

125
00:07:21,227 --> 00:07:22,227
Who cares.

126
00:07:22,227 --> 00:07:24,427
Shut up!

127
00:07:24,427 --> 00:07:26,627
You come back after a long while,

128
00:07:26,627 --> 00:07:29,427
and all you both do is talk about money!

129
00:07:29,427 --> 00:07:32,627
Wrong. I came because I was worried about you.

130
00:07:32,627 --> 00:07:34,027
Don't lie!

131
00:07:34,027 --> 00:07:35,827
I already heard that the import car dealer

132
00:07:35,827 --> 00:07:38,927
that you just started is suffering financially!

133
00:07:39,927 --> 00:07:41,727
Worry, my foot.

134
00:07:41,727 --> 00:07:45,427
It's no use fawning upon the great to win his favor.

135
00:07:45,427 --> 00:07:48,627
All he has in mind are his cactuses.

136
00:07:49,527 --> 00:07:52,427
No use picking a fight now.

137
00:07:52,427 --> 00:07:53,827
Let's cool it for now,

138
00:07:53,827 --> 00:07:56,227
and try convincing him later tonight.

139
00:07:56,227 --> 00:07:58,927
We're back.

140
00:08:00,627 --> 00:08:04,227
After looking through all the plants, I'm kind of hungry.

141
00:08:04,227 --> 00:08:05,227
Really.

142
00:08:05,227 --> 00:08:08,427
"It's cake before flowers" is a phrase made just for you.

143
00:08:11,027 --> 00:08:13,227
Conan!

144
00:08:13,227 --> 00:08:14,527
Are you all right?

145
00:08:14,527 --> 00:08:16,527
Hey! What do you think you're doing?

146
00:08:16,527 --> 00:08:19,027
-I'm sorry. -Gosh.

147
00:08:19,027 --> 00:08:21,127
I'm really sorry.

148
00:08:24,127 --> 00:08:26,027
This...

149
00:08:27,227 --> 00:08:28,927
Thanks.

150
00:08:28,927 --> 00:08:30,527
Ms. Yashiro.

151
00:08:30,527 --> 00:08:32,327
Yes, sir.

152
00:08:32,327 --> 00:08:34,527
Please bring my dinner to my room.

153
00:08:34,527 --> 00:08:37,027
Yes, sir.

154
00:08:37,027 --> 00:08:39,127
Yasuyuki really changed.

155
00:08:39,127 --> 00:08:41,327
I don't like him.

156
00:08:44,627 --> 00:08:46,727
I'm filled.

157
00:08:46,727 --> 00:08:49,027
I really ate.

158
00:08:49,027 --> 00:08:50,827
Sonoko, you ate too much.

159
00:08:50,827 --> 00:08:52,527
You took one helping after the other.

160
00:08:52,527 --> 00:08:53,827
I couldn't help it.

161
00:08:53,827 --> 00:08:56,527
When you got the craving, is when to go for it.

162
00:08:56,527 --> 00:08:58,227
Ms. Yashiro.

163
00:08:58,227 --> 00:08:59,227
Yes, sir?

164
00:08:59,227 --> 00:09:02,827
I'll go out to practice golf for a while.

165
00:09:02,827 --> 00:09:06,327
I'm going to go check on the car that I left back in the garage.

166
00:09:06,327 --> 00:09:09,127
Bye.

167
00:09:09,127 --> 00:09:12,327
Ms. Yashiro, thank you for the dinner.

168
00:09:12,327 --> 00:09:14,227
It was really delicious.

169
00:09:14,227 --> 00:09:17,827
Will you please teach me the recipe for that gravy sauce?

170
00:09:17,827 --> 00:09:21,527
Oh? Just who are you going to make it for?

171
00:09:21,527 --> 00:09:23,727
Don't tell me you're making it for your hubby.

172
00:09:23,727 --> 00:09:26,927
No. Come off it, Sonoko.

173
00:09:26,927 --> 00:09:29,727
I'm glad that you liked it.

174
00:09:29,727 --> 00:09:31,927
Would you like some coffee now?

175
00:09:31,927 --> 00:09:34,927
But we were just thinking of leaving.

176
00:09:34,927 --> 00:09:37,527
Is Mr. Sunada still in the greenhouse?

177
00:09:37,527 --> 00:09:40,027
Yes. Every day from about 20:00 to 21:00,

178
00:09:40,027 --> 00:09:43,127
he spends his time taking care of the cactuses.

179
00:09:43,127 --> 00:09:44,827
Let's go tell him goodbye, then.

180
00:09:44,827 --> 00:09:49,627
But I've told not to let anyone in until 20:30.

181
00:09:49,627 --> 00:09:52,127
So, could you wait a little while more?

182
00:09:52,127 --> 00:09:55,227
Okay then, I guess we'll take a eating break here for a while longer!

183
00:09:55,227 --> 00:09:56,927
I wonder if I'll get fat?

184
00:09:56,927 --> 00:09:59,627
Come on, Sonoko.

185
00:09:59,627 --> 00:10:01,627
That's nothing new.

186
00:10:10,427 --> 00:10:12,427
Yasuyuki?

187
00:10:12,427 --> 00:10:14,427
Wrong! I didn't do it!

188
00:10:14,427 --> 00:10:16,827
What's the matter?

189
00:10:16,827 --> 00:10:18,227
What's that?

190
00:10:18,227 --> 00:10:20,227
Isn't that the will?

191
00:10:20,227 --> 00:10:22,327
This is...

192
00:10:22,327 --> 00:10:24,127
Don't tell me that...

193
00:10:27,727 --> 00:10:29,327
Mr. Sunada!

194
00:10:30,427 --> 00:10:32,727
Mr. Sunada!

195
00:10:38,636 --> 00:10:41,636
The cause of death seems to be from a fractured skull

196
00:10:41,636 --> 00:10:43,736
from being beaten in the head with a shovel.

197
00:10:43,736 --> 00:10:45,636
The estimated time of death

198
00:10:45,636 --> 00:10:50,036
seems to be between 20:00 to 20:30.

199
00:10:50,036 --> 00:10:52,936
And who was the first to find the body...

200
00:10:54,436 --> 00:10:58,336
Gosh. I sure run into you kids a lot at the scenes of crimes.

201
00:10:58,336 --> 00:11:02,036
Hey, tell me about the circumstances when you found the body.

202
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:03,636
Uh...

203
00:11:03,636 --> 00:11:06,736
After dinner, we were chatting in the living room,

204
00:11:06,736 --> 00:11:07,736
when at about 20:00,

205
00:11:07,736 --> 00:11:10,136
the sound of the alarm in the greenhouse went off.

206
00:11:10,136 --> 00:11:14,436
Then, we went to look together with the housekeeper, Ms. Yashiro.

207
00:11:14,436 --> 00:11:17,836
And saw Yasuyuki there.

208
00:11:17,836 --> 00:11:19,436
You saw Yasuyuki?

209
00:11:19,436 --> 00:11:24,336
Yasuyuki was holding Mr. Sunada's will!

210
00:11:24,336 --> 00:11:25,836
Will?

211
00:11:25,836 --> 00:11:30,736
It seems that Mr. Sunada recently rewrote the will!

212
00:11:31,736 --> 00:11:35,336
Then, right after that, Misa ran into the greenhouse

213
00:11:35,336 --> 00:11:38,236
and when we all followed her inside...

214
00:11:38,236 --> 00:11:40,236
Mr. Sunada was...

215
00:11:41,536 --> 00:11:44,436
Hey, let's go interrogate the people involved!

216
00:11:44,436 --> 00:11:45,536
Yes, sir.

217
00:11:45,536 --> 00:11:46,636
Like I already told you,

218
00:11:46,636 --> 00:11:49,536
I rushed inside because I heard the alarm

219
00:11:49,536 --> 00:11:51,636
and found Dad lying on the floor!

220
00:11:51,636 --> 00:11:54,036
Why were you in the greenhouse

221
00:11:54,036 --> 00:11:56,036
when you said you were going out to practice golf?

222
00:11:56,036 --> 00:11:59,836
That's because Dad texted me to come over.

223
00:11:59,836 --> 00:12:02,836
See!

224
00:12:02,836 --> 00:12:04,236
I see.

225
00:12:04,236 --> 00:12:07,136
You received it at 20:20.

226
00:12:07,136 --> 00:12:08,836
How about the victim's cell phone?

227
00:12:08,836 --> 00:12:13,436
Likewise, at 20:20 he texted to Yasuyuki.

228
00:12:13,436 --> 00:12:18,236
Which means that the old man was alive till then.

229
00:12:18,236 --> 00:12:20,936
And, what about the will?

230
00:12:20,936 --> 00:12:25,336
Weren't you standing in front of the greenhouse holding the will?

231
00:12:25,336 --> 00:12:27,236
Well...

232
00:12:27,236 --> 00:12:29,636
I took it from the pocket of Dad who was lying on the ground.

233
00:12:29,636 --> 00:12:31,636
Which means that you...

234
00:12:31,636 --> 00:12:34,236
Wrong! I didn't do it! Please believe me!

235
00:12:34,236 --> 00:12:38,236
This was found near the corpse.

236
00:12:38,236 --> 00:12:39,636
A golf tee!

237
00:12:39,636 --> 00:12:42,236
That's Yasuyuki's...

238
00:12:42,236 --> 00:12:43,236
Yasuyuki!

239
00:12:43,236 --> 00:12:44,836
Beats me.

240
00:12:44,836 --> 00:12:47,836
Why would something like that be in a place like this?

241
00:12:47,836 --> 00:12:50,536
Please believe me! I didn't do it!

242
00:12:50,536 --> 00:12:52,736
I didn't kill Dad!

243
00:12:52,736 --> 00:12:54,236
Please believe me!

244
00:12:54,236 --> 00:12:56,236
After being texted to come here by the victim,

245
00:12:56,236 --> 00:12:59,936
you pretended to go practice golfing

246
00:12:59,936 --> 00:13:02,136
and headed for the greenhouse.

247
00:13:02,136 --> 00:13:03,636
The victim let you in,

248
00:13:03,636 --> 00:13:06,836
but you got into an argument with him concerning the will.

249
00:13:06,836 --> 00:13:09,236
You lost your temper and picked up the shovel that was by you

250
00:13:09,236 --> 00:13:12,336
and beat Mr. Sunada to death!

251
00:13:12,336 --> 00:13:17,136
You took the will to gain inheritance, then fled.

252
00:13:18,036 --> 00:13:22,536
Back then, the alarm sensed you and it went off!

253
00:13:22,536 --> 00:13:25,036
-Isn't that what happened? -No way.

254
00:13:25,036 --> 00:13:28,136
Inspector Yokomizo.

255
00:13:28,136 --> 00:13:30,136
Mr. Sunada should've had a card

256
00:13:30,136 --> 00:13:33,736
to cancel the alarm in his pocket, you know.

257
00:13:33,736 --> 00:13:37,036
I wonder why that wasn't taken?

258
00:13:37,036 --> 00:13:40,536
If he used it, the alarm wouldn't have gone off, don't you think?

259
00:13:42,236 --> 00:13:45,136
It's true that the card to cancel the alarm

260
00:13:45,136 --> 00:13:47,636
was in the victim's pocket.

261
00:13:47,636 --> 00:13:51,236
You probably just panicked after beating your Dad up.

262
00:13:51,236 --> 00:13:53,336
-Isn't that right? -There's more.

263
00:13:53,336 --> 00:13:54,936
What is it now?

264
00:13:54,936 --> 00:13:56,436
There's the planter of the Hairbrush Cactus

265
00:13:56,436 --> 00:13:59,436
on the ground near Mr. Sunada, isn't there?

